1.00	Algernon_Capell,_2nd_Earl_of_Essex	Algernon Capell, 2nd Earl of Essex	Algernon Capell, 2nd Earl of Essex PC (28 December 1670 â€“ 10 January 1710, Watford) was an English nobleman, a soldier and courtier. He was the son of Arthur Capell, 1st Earl of Essex and Elizabeth Percy. After his father's suicide in 1683, Capell became the 2nd Earl of Essex. He held the office of Gentleman of the Bedchamber to King William III between 1691 and 1702; was Colonel of the 4th Dragoons between 1693 and 1710; and was made a Privy Counselor in 1708 by Queen Anne.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e4/Algernon_Capel%2C_2nd_Earl_of_Essex_by_Sir_Godfrey_Kneller%2C_Bt.jpg/200px-Algernon_Capel%2C_2nd_Earl_of_Essex_by_Sir_Godfrey_Kneller%2C_Bt.jpg
